div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hpa1665702942777.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hpa1665702942777.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hpa1665702942777.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hpa1665702942777\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configure Uniface for LDAP\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To configure Uniface to connect to with LDAP, you need to edit the Uniface application assignment file.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__li_d24554e1_d24555e1_d24556e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51548e1_d51549e1_d51550e1\">In the assignment file, specify the LDAP connector version you want to use in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS ] section. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nLDP = U3.0\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__li_d24557e1_d24558e1_d24559e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51551e1_d51552e1_d51553e1\">Optionally, specify options to modify the\n               behavior of the LDAP connector using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS</span>. For example:\n               For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rht1665702724463.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rht1665702724463.html\" title=\"You can assign LDAP connector options using the USYS$LDP_PARAMS setting in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS] section of the assignment file.\">LDAP Connector Options</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nLDP = U3.0\nUSYS$LDP_PARAMS tls server validation=ignore_name, nulldefault=N</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__li_d24560e1_d24561e1_d24562e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51554e1_d51555e1_d51556e1\">Define the logon path in the [PATHS ] section. For example:\n \n <code class=\"ph codeph\">www.traders.com</code>is the server acting as host, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">o=accounting.com</code>is the organization used as the LDAP search base.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$LDP LDP:www.traders.com+389:o=accounting.com| |</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__li_d24563e1_d24564e1_d24565e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51557e1_d51558e1_d51559e1\">Define entity settings in the [ENTITIES] section to determine at which level of the LDAP tree entries are stored.\n Entity settings in the assignment file have the following syntax:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity.Model</var> = <var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>@<var class=\"keyword varname\">Tree.Model</var>\n               </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51560e1_d51561e1_d51562e1\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">person.ldap = person@ou=People,o=name.com.*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51563e1_d51564e1_d51565e1\">If this information is not specified, the path search base is used, in which case all database operations default to this level in the LDAP tree. Searches start here and new entries are stored at this level.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51566e1_d51567e1_d51568e1\">Due to the nature of LDAP, the LDAP connector tries to store updated entries at this level even when they have been retrieved from a different level. To circumvent this behavior, it is possible to use entity redirecting to store entries at the correct level.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51569e1_d51570e1_d51571e1\">Consider an LDAP tree which is structured as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">o=accounting.com\nou=people ou=finance</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hpa1665702942777__p_d51572e1_d51573e1_d51574e1\">The following settings ensure that the <code class=\"ph codeph\">person</code>entity is stored at the search base level, while the <code class=\"ph codeph\">person2</code>entity is redirected to another node.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$LDP = LDP:www.traders.com+389:o=accounting.com|eddie|eddie\n[ENTITIES]\nperson.ldap=person@o=accounting.com\nperson2.ldap=person@ou=people,o=accounting.com\n*.ldap = $LDP:*.*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pfs1665702941848.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP</a><p>The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528317\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configure Uniface for LDAP Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configure Uniface for LDAP To configure Uniface to connect to with LDAP, you need to edit the Uniface application assignment file. In the assignment file, specify the LDAP connector version you want to use in the [DRIVER_SETTINGS ] section. For example: [DRIVER_SETTINGS] LDP = U3.0 Copy Optionally, specify options to modify the behavior of the LDAP connector using USYS$LDP_PARAMS . For example: For more information, see LDAP Connector Options . [DRIVER_SETTINGS] LDP = U3.0 USYS$LDP_PARAMS tls server validation=ignore_name, nulldefault=N Copy Define the logon path in the [PATHS ] section. For example: www.traders.com is the server acting as host, and o=accounting.com is the organization used as the LDAP search base. [PATHS] $LDP LDP:www.traders.com+389:o=accounting.com| | Copy Define entity settings in the [ENTITIES] section to determine at which level of the LDAP tree entries are stored. Entity settings in the assignment file have the following syntax: Entity.Model = Entity @ Tree.Model Copy For example: person.ldap = person@ou=People,o=name.com.* Copy If this information is not specified, the path search base is used, in which case all database operations default to this level in the LDAP tree. Searches start here and new entries are stored at this level. Due to the nature of LDAP, the LDAP connector tries to store updated entries at this level even when they have been retrieved from a different level. To circumvent this behavior, it is possible to use entity redirecting to store entries at the correct level. Consider an LDAP tree which is structured as follows: o=accounting.com ou=people ou=finance Copy The following settings ensure that the person entity is stored at the search base level, while the person2 entity is redirected to another node. [PATHS] $LDP = LDP:www.traders.com+389:o=accounting.com|eddie|eddie [ENTITIES] person.ldap=person@o=accounting.com person2.ldap=person@ou=people,o=accounting.com *.ldap = $LDP:*.* Copy Related Links LDAP The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}